{SECT 0 {PARA 256 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 14 "DeSanne Fluitt" }}{PARA 256 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 20 "4-7-03, Worksheet 03" }}{PARA 256 "" 0 "" {TEXT 276 
37 "Binomial Theorem  & Solving Equations" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 179 "Save your current worksheet as wo
rk03-yourlastname.mws.  Remember to save frequently to avoid losing da
ta in case that the system would shut down in the middle of a work ses
sion! " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
104 "In the text mode (click on the cap T button) place your name(s) a
nd date at the top of your worksheet.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 
"" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
46 "1.  Binomial Theorem.  Use the Maple command  " }{TEXT 262 6 "expa
nd" }{TEXT 256 2 "  " }{TEXT -1 34 "to calculate the expansion of     \+
" }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)^n;" "6#),&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&%\"nG" }{TEXT -1 
63 "    for values n=1..10 .  In each case use the Maple command   " }
{TEXT 257 7 "coeffs " }{TEXT 264 1 " " }{TEXT -1 84 "to pick off the c
oefficients.   For example,  if n=5 we would execute the following:" }
}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 27 "expand((a+b)^5);\ncoeffs(%
);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,.*$)%\"aG\"\"&\"\"\"F(*(F'F()F&
\"\"%F(%\"bGF(F(*(\"#5F()F&\"\"$F()F,\"\"#F(F(*(F.F()F&F2F()F,F0F(F(*(
F'F(F&F()F,F+F(F(*$)F,F'F(F(" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6(\"\"&
\"\"\"F$\"#5F%F#" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 28 "Do the rest from 1 t
o 10.   " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 31 "Note:  it is possible to use \+
a " }{TEXT 263 9 "for loop " }{TEXT -1 69 " to simplify this task sinc
e we are doing a repetitive calculation.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 29 "Note:  Also, the the command " }{TEXT 265 6 "coeffs" }{TEXT -1 
15 " unfortunately " }{TEXT 266 8 "does not" }{TEXT -1 36 " pick off t
he coefficients in order." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "The " }{TEXT 259 16 "Binomial Theorem" }{TEXT -1 
66 " gives a formula for finding the coefficients of the expansion of \+
" }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)^n;" "6#),&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&%\"nG" }{TEXT -1 
10 "  for any " }{TEXT 267 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 53 ".  It is relatively obv
ious that the coefficient of  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "a^(n-k)*b^k;" "6#*&)%
\"aG,&%\"nG\"\"\"%\"kG!\"\"F()%\"bGF)F(" }{TEXT -1 19 "  for any value
 of " }{TEXT 268 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 11 " from 0 to " }{TEXT 269 1 "n" }
{TEXT -1 46 " is given by the number of ways we can choose " }{TEXT 
270 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 8 " of the " }{TEXT 294 1 "b" }{TEXT -1 12 "'s fro
m the " }{TEXT 271 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 1 " " }{TEXT 295 1 "b" }{TEXT -1 
20 "'s in the expansion " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)*(a+b)" "6#*&,&%\"aG\"
\"\"%\"bGF&F&,&F%F&F'F&F&" }{TEXT -1 7 " ....( " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)
" "6#,&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF%" }{TEXT -1 5 " ),  " }{TEXT 272 1 "n" }
{TEXT -1 41 " times .   The number of combinations of " }{TEXT 273 1 "
n" }{TEXT -1 18 " objects choosing " }{TEXT 274 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 12 " a
t a time, " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "nCk" "6#%$nCkG" }{TEXT -1 27 ", is given b
y the formula  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "nCk=n!/(k!*(n-k)!)" "6#/%$nCkG*&-%*fa
ctorialG6#%\"nG\"\"\"*&-F'6#%\"kGF*-F'6#,&F)F*F.!\"\"F*F2" }{TEXT -1 
2 " ." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 261 10 
"State the " }{TEXT 260 16 "Binomial Theorem" }{TEXT -1 1 " " }{TEXT 
275 31 "and use Maple to demonstrate it" }{TEXT -1 1 "." }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "f1:=(a+
b)^n;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#f1G),&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF(%
\"nG" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 42 "for n from 1 to 10
